Beijing faces a water crisis with more residents than available supply.
China aims to reduce water consumption by 20% by 2010 due to economic growth and population increase straining resources.
The government plans water-saving projects and quotas to manage usage.
Despite increased grain production, China still faces shortages and may become a net food importer.
Climate change threatens China's agriculture and water supply, with rising temperatures and reduced crop yields predicted.
